Elizabeth and her Children, 1699-1736 301

My Brother remembers to you all. [On reverse of RMA, Selmes Manuscripts, RYEYT N39.59.2]

Dear Sister

I have according to your desire bought you Waller’s Poems” for which I gave 2s. I would fain have got it cheaper but could not, however I think it is as good as mine which cost 2s 6d. If at any time you have any business wherein I can be serviceable to you; Please to let me know it and it shall be willingly per- formed by

Your Loving Brother Francis Jeake

London August the 8" 1716 [like my place very well. Pray give my Duty to my Father & remember me to all my Friends at Rye.

Please to give my Love to Sister Phill & tell her I expect her to perform her promise.

I have now sent per Carrier Ipair of Shoes

% oz of Gold thread Wallers Poems

To Madam Tucker at Rye in Sussex
